ENGLISH.QUESTION_TEXT: Which of the following statements is incorrect regarding pouring of molten metal in mould cavity?
ENGLISH.OPT1: The temperature at which pouring is done is around 20% more than the melting temperature of the metal.
ENGLISH.OPT2: Higher the pouring temperature, higher is the fluidity of the metal.
ENGLISH.OPT3: If the pouring rate is too slow, the tendency of formation of metal oxides is more which can get entrapped during solidification.
ENGLISH.OPT4: If the pouring rate is too high, turbulence can occur in molten metal flow.

ENGLISH.QUESTION_TEXT: Which of the following is not an advantage of powder metallurgy processing?
ENGLISH.OPT1: Such processing involves little wastage of raw material.
ENGLISH.OPT2: Such processing produces near net shape products.
ENGLISH.OPT3: The raw material being in powdered form is easy to store and handle.
ENGLISH.OPT4: Difficult to fabricate materials like tungsten can be readily shaped using such processing method.

ENGLISH.QUESTION_TEXT: Which of the following is a set of desirable properties for a metal to be easily formed?
ENGLISH.OPT1: Low yield strength and high ductility
ENGLISH.OPT2: High yield strength and high ductility
ENGLISH.OPT3: High yield strength and low ductility
ENGLISH.OPT4: Low yield strength and high ductility

ENGLISH.QUESTION_TEXT: Which of the following are correct settings of power source in resistance welding?
ENGLISH.OPT1: Low current; High voltage; Short duration
ENGLISH.OPT2: High current; Low voltage; Short duration
ENGLISH.OPT3: High current; Low voltage; Long duration
ENGLISH.OPT4: High current; High voltage; Short duration
